Baduki

BA: word/syllable/sound
DU: collection
KI: the

Baduki is the language of the Kekelplithfs

---------------------------------

Kekelplithf

KE : two
KEL : blade
PLITHF : rizen

---------------------------------

Brekelēga

BRE : martial
KEL : blade
Ē : feeling/awareness
GA : move

ĒGA : dance

The Brekelēga dance utilizes the Kekelplithfs' finblades as weapons.

---------------------------------

Syllables:

BA: word/syllable/sound/aum
BO: Great/Good/Beautiful
BREK : martial
DAN: thanks/gratitude
DU: collection
Ē : feeling/awareness/consience
FROP : frop
GA : movement
GRO : ground
HAM : Exchange
HU : Fear/Unease
-KI: the
KE : two
KEL : blade
PLITHF : rizen/supported by/elevated
TO : material / resource
WAR : Wolf
YI : person/entity
YO : special

MI : I / me / mine
UM : we / us / our
YU : you / your (singular)
ZU : you / your (plural)
DE : he
DA : they / them / their

word | verb | noun
------------------
MI | I | mine
UM | we | our
YU | you | your
ZU | you | your


